org.latency4j

Class StatisticalLatencyRequirement

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.latency4j.LatencyRequirement
      • org.latency4j.StatisticalLatencyRequirement

  • public class StatisticalLatencyRequirement
extends LatencyRequirement

    A statistical requirement can be used in situations where there is no specific upper bound for operation latency, but monitoring is required to identify operation latencies which deviate from an observed pattern. Put differently, this type of requirement is suited for situations where operation latency should not deviate by more than a given margin from an observed average.

    • Method Detail

      • getObservationsSignificanceBarrier

        public long getObservationsSignificanceBarrier()

        Returns the number of observations with which monitors of the requirement are to be calibrated initially.

        Monitors will use this number of executions to observe the behaviour of the application and determine parameters such as average execution latency. As such, observance of the requirement will not be checked until this barrier is reached.

        For example, if a value of 10 is returned by this method, it means that the first 10 invocations falling within this requirement are used purely for calibration. All subsequent requests will then be judged based on figures calculated from these first ten.

        Note: Monitors continuously re-calibrate during the lifetime of an application. As such, calibration does not stop entirely after this number of requests is observed. Instead, these requests are used as a starting point.

        Returns:
        The number of observations with which monitors of this requirement are initially calibrated.
        See Also:
        AlertHandler.latencyDeviationExceededTolerance(StatisticalLatencyRequirement, WorkDuration, double, double)

      • getToleranceLevel

        public double getToleranceLevel()

        Returns the tolerance level within which operation execution times must fall in order not to be in breach of the requirement.

        A task invocation with a duration of x milliseconds is considered to have breached its requirement if the following inequality holds:
        (x - averageLatency) > averageLatency * getToleranceLevel().
        In other words, the deviation from the average latency must be below a given percentage of said average. Else the operation is treated as having breached the requirement, thus triggering an alert.

        Returns:
        The latency/duration tolerance level to be applied to latency observations governed by the requirement.
        See Also:
        AlertHandler.latencyDeviationExceededTolerance(StatisticalLatencyRequirement, WorkDuration, double, double)
